metadata.name: Battle of Hybloricus
metadata.description:
Hybloricus City was built among the high mountains and was truly an ever-growing metropolis.  
Its elegance with the background of misty mountains and black clouds added a certain grandeur to the city.  
The climate these skies brought was of great importance, 
but they were also influential when it came to architectural designs as the vast majority of buildings have been built to great heights, 
as if to try and reach the blue skies above them.  
But now the once great city is filled with weapons, blood, and body parts. Red, Silver, and khaki are the new colors of a city that was once a symbol of beauty and grandeur but has now become the scene of a brutal war.  
The air that normally carried the voices of well-dressed people of royal blood and big tools was now deafeningly loud, the screeching drowning out every other sound in the area, a sight of pure nightmares.  
aaah... 
Wars.. wars... wars...  
They were always around the corner,  
and we will never see any end to this. 


8192 x 8192px
